## Description {#details}

Abstract concept of an analysis result.

This concept is parameterized over the IR unit that this result pertains to.

## Public Member Functions

### invalidate() {#aed810e47a1f277849f34ba839bd8a587}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename IRUnitT, typename InvalidatorT&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>virtual bool llvm::detail::AnalysisResultConcept&lt; IRUnitT, InvalidatorT &gt;::invalidate (IRUnitT &amp; IR, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/preservedanalyses">PreservedAnalyses</a> &amp; PA, InvalidatorT &amp; Inv)</>}>
Method to try and mark a result as invalid.

When the outer analysis manager detects a change in some underlying unit of the IR, it will call this method on all of the results cached.

<code>PA</code> is a set of preserved analyses which can be used to avoid invalidation because the pass which changed the underlying IR took care to update or preserve the analysis result in some way.

<code>Inv</code> is typically a <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/analysismanager/invalidator">AnalysisManager::Invalidator</a></code> object that can be used by a particular analysis result to discover if other analyses results are also invalidated in the event that this result depends on them. See the documentation in the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/analysismanager">AnalysisManager</a></code> for more details.


<SectionUser title="Returns">
true if the result is indeed invalid (the default).
</SectionUser>
